    "ocr_text": "LF
Sept. 10, 1909

Mr. Harry L. Cook,
c/o D. F. Featherson,
142 East 59th St., New York, N.Y.

Dear Sir:

In the absence of President Gompers I beg to acknowledge receipt of your favor of September 9th, in which you enclose clipping from the Newark Star of September 6th. You will please accept Mr. Gompers' thanks for your courtesy.

Very truly yours
[Signature]
Secretary to President Gompers.",
    "summary": "The letter, dated September 10, 1909, acknowledges receipt of a previous letter from September 9th, which included a newspaper clipping from the Newark Star dated September 6th. The sender extends thanks on behalf of President Gompers.",
